   {:e #blake3 "1a87f6bfebed30f15b1a1eccfa9cd57baea26825e6bcb1266a9c13ccb2070e7f" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :task/t-29eb725d; FAILURE MODE DIAGNOSIS: Why braid observe failed to surface ACP-related specs/tasks when creating TSV and CTP observations. Root cause: knowledge_relevance_scan() in guidance.rs uses keyword_alignment_score() (Jaccard similarity of bag-of-words) for the 'related:' output. The TSV observations used terms like 'output format', 'tab separated', 'density', 'rendering' — which have LOW Jaccard overlap with ACP observations that use terms like 'action centric', 'projection', 'budget', 'activation'. The two CONCEPT CLUSTERS are semantically synonymous but lexically disjoint. Jaccard similarity is 0 between 'TSV rendering pipeline' and 'Action-Centric Projection' because they share zero keywords despite being about the SAME architectural concern (output formatting). This is SEMANTIC DIVERGENCE (Reconciliation Taxonomy Type 5, Logical) — the same concept expressed in different vocabulary. The fix requires: (1) Semantic similarity (embeddings) instead of lexical (Jaccard). (2) OR: transitivity through shared spec refs — both TSV and ACP reference INV-INTERFACE-001, so they should be connected via the spec graph even when keywords don't overlap. The spec graph IS the shared vocabulary that bridges lexical gaps.; REVISION AFTER DEEP AUDIT: Two critical flaws found in crystallized tasks. FLAW 1: TSV-2 proposed adding tsv: String field to CommandOutput — wrong. TSV should be a render-time format computed from the existing JSON/ACP structure, not a parallel data field. The JSON already contains all structured data. TSV rendering = flatten JSON arrays to rows + fields to columns. This means TSV-2 needs zero changes to CommandOutput struct — only OutputMode enum + render() match arm + a json_to_tsv(json, field_spec) utility function. FLAW 2: CTP tasks proposed replacing seed architecture — wrong. The seed already has ContextSection::{Orientation, Constraints, State, Warnings, Directive} — which IS the four-field structure. The upgrades are to the SELECTION ALGORITHMS within each section, not new data types. CTP-1 upgrades Orientation content, CTP-2 upgrades Constraints selection, CTP-3 enriches State with demonstrations, CTP-4 upgrades Directive content, CTP-5 replaces the selection heuristics in assemble(). This is evolution, not revolution — preserving the existing architecture while upgrading the intelligence behind each section.\nSession entity: :task/t-3f0f3ef1; Session entity: :task/t-7286ed7d; Session entity: :task/t-41696627; Session entity: :task/t-827dbbb8; Session entity: :task/t-c1f8e354" :op :assert}
